Create frame in Java?
A Frame is a top-level window with a title and a border.
The size of the frame includes any area designated for the border.
he dimensions of the border area may be obtained using the getInsets method.
 Since the border area is included in the overall size of the frame, the border effectively obscures a portion of the frame, constraining the area available
